            <div type="content">
                <div type="index">
                <p>
                    <specList>
                        <specDesc key="lg"/>
                    </specList>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <p>Important: <gi>lg</gi> should be specified by a <att>type</att> attribute, whose value(s) listed here are the only being currently handled by SigiDoc/EFES
                    autority lists and they should be used as they appear here:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <lg type="metrical" ana=""><l/></lg>
                </egXML>
                <p>Notice that here the attribute pointing to the authority list is <att>ana</att> (and not <att>ref</att>).</p>
                <p>If the metrical legend is spanned over the two faces of the seal, <gi>lg</gi> should be duplicated on the 2 faces
                    (because the latter are encoded in two separate <gi>div</gi>s) for a proper tagging, but in the second the <att>ref</att> to the authority list shouldn’t be added,
                    otherwise the index would display 2 entries for the same metrical legend.</p>
                <p>See also "<ref target="SigiDoc_struct-verseline.html">Verse lines</ref>".</p>
            </div>
            </div>
